1) """Indexing with a Boolean Expression."""
How It Works?
    If temp == rev is True (1), it prints "Yes" (index 1).
    If temp == rev is False (0), it prints "No" (index 0).
    Example:
        temp = 121
        rev = 121
        print(("No", "Yes")[temp == rev])  # Output: Yes
        
        temp = 123
        rev = 321
        print(("No", "Yes")[temp == rev])  # Output: No

