      Instead of:
          n = input("Enter a number: ")
          if n.isdigit():
              print("You entered:", n)
      You can do this in one line using the walrus operator (:=):
          if (n := input("Enter a number: ")).isdigit():
              print("You entered:", n)
      
      n := input("Enter a number: ") assigns the value inside the if condition.
      So, you donâ€™t need a separate line for assignment!
